---
import ServiceLayout from '../../layouts/ServiceLayout.astro';
---

<ServiceLayout
  title="Underfloor Heating Wellington | Rohullah Rassuli Tiling"
  description="Underfloor heating installation in Wellington. Electric heating mats under tiles for warm, comfortable bathrooms and kitchens. Free quotes — call 021 026 02044."
  canonical="/services/underfloor-heating"
  serviceName="Underfloor Heating"
  serviceType="Underfloor Heating Installation"
  serviceDescription="Electric underfloor heating installation beneath tiles in Wellington for warm, comfortable bathrooms, kitchens, and living areas."
>

  <!-- Intro Section -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="split-layout fade-in-up">
        <div>
          <p class="lead">
            There is nothing worse than stepping onto cold tiles on a Wellington winter morning. Electric underfloor heating transforms your tiled floors from cold and uninviting to warm and comfortable — making bathrooms, kitchens, and living areas a pleasure to use all year round.
          </p>
          <p>
            Rohullah Rassuli Tiling Services installs electric underfloor heating systems beneath tiles as part of new tiling projects and renovations. The heating mats or cables are laid directly onto the substrate, embedded in tile adhesive, and covered with your chosen tiles. The result is invisible, silent warmth that radiates evenly across the entire floor surface.
          </p>
          <p>
            Wellington's climate — with cold, damp winters and average daily minimums dropping to 6-7 degrees from June to August — makes underfloor heating one of the smartest comfort upgrades you can make to your home.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="image-placeholder image-placeholder--portrait">
            <span>Underfloor heating mat installation</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Services -->
  <section class="section section--light">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">Underfloor Heating Services</h2>
      <p class="section-subtitle">Professional installation of electric underfloor heating beneath tiles in any room.</p>

      <div class="services-grid">
        <div class="service-card fade-in-up">
          <h3>Bathroom Underfloor Heating</h3>
          <p>The most popular application. Warm bathroom floors eliminate the shock of cold tiles after a shower and help reduce condensation and moisture in the room — a real benefit in Wellington's humid climate.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="service-card fade-in-up">
          <h3>Kitchen Floor Heating</h3>
          <p>Spend more time on your feet in the kitchen? Underfloor heating keeps things comfortable, especially in open-plan kitchen-living areas with tiled floors that can feel cold during winter months.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="service-card fade-in-up">
          <h3>Living Area Floor Heating</h3>
          <p>Large tiled living areas, hallways, and entrance foyers benefit enormously from underfloor heating. It provides gentle, ambient warmth without taking up wall space or drying out the air like traditional heaters.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="service-card fade-in-up">
          <h3>Ensuite &amp; Powder Room Heating</h3>
          <p>Even small spaces make a big difference. A heated ensuite or powder room floor is an affordable luxury that adds comfort and value to your Wellington home.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="service-card fade-in-up">
          <h3>Laundry Floor Heating</h3>
          <p>Keep your laundry warm and help clothes dry faster in winter. Underfloor heating in the laundry also reduces condensation on tiled surfaces and walls.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="service-card fade-in-up">
          <h3>Commercial Underfloor Heating</h3>
          <p>Medical clinics, day spas, hair salons, and hospitality venues — anywhere your clients or customers will appreciate warm floors and a comfortable environment.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Benefits Section -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">Benefits of Underfloor Heating</h2>
      <p class="section-subtitle">Why Wellington homeowners are choosing heated tile floors.</p>

      <div class="services-grid fade-in-up">
        <div class="service-card">
          <h3>Comfortable Warmth</h3>
          <p>Heat radiates evenly from the entire floor surface, warming the room from the ground up. No cold spots, no draughts, and no waiting for the room to heat up — tiles retain and distribute warmth efficiently.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="service-card">
          <h3>Energy Efficient</h3>
          <p>Electric underfloor heating in a bathroom typically costs just 5-10 cents per hour to run. Combined with a programmable thermostat, you can schedule heating to coincide with your morning and evening routines.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="service-card">
          <h3>Invisible Installation</h3>
          <p>Once tiles are laid over the heating mats, the system is completely invisible. No radiators, no wall panels, no visible heaters — just warm floors and clean, uncluttered walls.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="service-card">
          <h3>Reduced Moisture &amp; Mould</h3>
          <p>Warm floors help reduce condensation in bathrooms and wet areas. In Wellington's humid climate, this is a real advantage for keeping bathrooms dry and minimising mould growth.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="service-card">
          <h3>Added Property Value</h3>
          <p>Heated bathroom and living area floors are a sought-after feature in Wellington's property market. It is a relatively modest investment that adds genuine comfort value for future buyers.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="service-card">
          <h3>Tile Compatibility</h3>
          <p>Electric underfloor heating works with all tile types — porcelain, ceramic, natural stone, and large-format tiles. Tiles are excellent conductors of heat, making them the ideal flooring material for heated floors.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Wellington Comfort Section -->
  <section class="section section--dark">
    <div class="container fade-in-up">
      <h2 class="section-title section-title--white">Warm Floors for Wellington Winters</h2>
      <p>
        Wellington is well known for its bracing winters. Southerly winds bring cold air straight from the Antarctic, and many Wellington homes — especially older villas and townhouses — struggle to stay warm. Tiled floors in bathrooms and kitchens can feel particularly cold, discouraging bare feet and making morning routines uncomfortable.
      </p>
      <p>
        Electric underfloor heating is the most effective solution for cold tiled floors. Unlike heat pumps that warm the air from above, underfloor heating warms the floor surface itself, so your feet are in direct contact with the warmth. The heat then rises gently into the room, creating a comfortable ambient temperature without the noise, draughts, or dry air associated with fan heaters and heat pumps.
      </p>
      <p>
        Many of our Wellington clients tell us that underfloor heating is the single best upgrade they have made to their home. Once you have experienced warm tiles underfoot on a cold July morning, you will wonder how you ever lived without it.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Process Section -->
  <section class="section section--light">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">Installation Process</h2>
      <p class="section-subtitle">How we install underfloor heating beneath your tiles.</p>

      <div class="process-timeline fade-in-up">
        <div class="process-step">
          <h4>1. Assessment &amp; Planning</h4>
          <p>We assess the room, measure the floor area, and plan the heating mat layout. We identify the thermostat location and coordinate with your electrician for the power supply connection.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="process-step">
          <h4>2. Substrate Preparation</h4>
          <p>The floor is levelled, cleaned, and primed. If waterproofing is required (in bathrooms and wet areas), it is applied and cured before the heating system is installed.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="process-step">
          <h4>3. Heating Mat Installation</h4>
          <p>Electric heating mats or loose cables are rolled out and secured to the floor according to the manufacturer's layout plan. We ensure even coverage and avoid overlap or damage to the heating elements.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="process-step">
          <h4>4. Testing</h4>
          <p>The heating system is electrically tested before tiling to confirm all elements are functioning correctly. Resistance readings are recorded and compared to manufacturer specifications.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="process-step">
          <h4>5. Tiling</h4>
          <p>Tiles are laid over the heating mats using flexible adhesive that accommodates thermal expansion. We take care not to damage the heating cables during the tiling process.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="process-step">
          <h4>6. Commissioning</h4>
          <p>After tiles and grout have fully cured (typically 7-14 days), the system is commissioned by a registered electrician. The thermostat is programmed and the system is ready to use.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Gallery Placeholder -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">Underfloor Heating Gallery</h2>
      <div class="services-grid fade-in-up">
        <div class="image-placeholder image-placeholder--landscape">
          <span>Heating mat laid in bathroom — Whitby</span>
        </div>
        <div class="image-placeholder image-placeholder--landscape">
          <span>Kitchen underfloor heating — Johnsonville</span>
        </div>
        <div class="image-placeholder image-placeholder--landscape">
          <span>Completed heated tile floor — Porirua</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Internal Links -->
  <section class="section section--light">
    <div class="container fade-in-up">
      <h2 class="section-title section-title--left">Related Services</h2>
      <p>
        Underfloor heating is most commonly installed as part of a <a href="/services/bathroom-tiling">bathroom tiling</a> or <a href="/services/floor-tiling">floor tiling</a> project. When combined with proper <a href="/services/waterproofing">waterproofing</a> in wet areas, you get a warm, dry, and fully code-compliant result.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you are renovating a kitchen, <a href="/services/kitchen-tiling">kitchen floor tiling</a> with underfloor heating is a popular combination that makes open-plan living spaces comfortable through Wellington's colder months.
      </p>
      <p>
        <a href="/contact">Contact us today</a> for a free consultation and quote on underfloor heating installation.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

</ServiceLayout>

<script>
  const observer = new IntersectionObserver(
    (entries) => {
      entries.forEach((entry) => {
        if (entry.isIntersecting) {
          entry.target.classList.add('visible');
        }
      });
    },
    { threshold: 0.1 }
  );

  document.querySelectorAll('.fade-in-up').forEach((el) => observer.observe(el));
</script>
